        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="pq0AM1h1IiiyBDEnBlEK-54" value="TODOs:&lt;div&gt;- somehow the GPT-2 with pretrained weights should just go through all training samples and generate a sequence of embedding vectors for all screenplays&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- the &quot;GPT version&quot; (&quot;chunky GPT&quot;) of the model takes an unfrozen trainable Transformer Decoder and learns to predict probability of nomination based on those pre-computed sequence of embedding vectors&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- embedding vectors will be generated in a manner similar to the Movie-o-Label&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fff2cc;strokeColor=#d6b656;verticalAlign=top;align=left;spacingLeft=6;spacingRight=6;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2320" y="160" width="200" height="280" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="pq0AM1h1IiiyBDEnBlEK-55" value="TODOs:&lt;div&gt;- consider pre-chunking the screenplays like Movie-o-Label paper: 400 word chunks (avg eq tokens) with 80 word overlap&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- all screenplays padded to end up with the same number of chunks&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- each chunk is then given to hierarchical transformer encoder, which produces a sequence of embedding vectors, one by one...&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fff2cc;strokeColor=#d6b656;verticalAlign=top;align=left;spacingLeft=6;spacingRight=6;fontStyle=2" parent="1" vertex="1">
